---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout hideNavbar={true}>

  <section class="min-h-screen px-6 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <h1 
        class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-shadow-purple text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
      >
        Collapse
      </h1>

      <p 
        class="text-lg text-gray-400 mb-12 text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
        data-aos-delay="100"
      >
        A short film inspired by Schrödinger's Cat — where four students walk into a classroom and reality stops behaving normally.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">

        <!-- Origin -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Where It Started</h2>
          <p>
            This was our Semester 4 “Vistas of Science through Films” project. 
            We knew we wanted to make a mystery thriller — something slightly unsettling.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The best idea was called out by yours truly and was called <span class="text-primary font-bold">"The Vanishing Room"</span> — 
            where few students enter a classroom and start disappearing one by one.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Turning point -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Twist</h2>
          <p>
            Then came the catch — we had to include a science fiction concept.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            That's where things got interesting. Instead of forcing sci-fi into the story, 
            we started thinking… what if the mystery itself *was* the science?
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Concept -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="400">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Connecting It to Schrödinger</h2>
          <p>
            We landed on Schrödinger's Cat — the idea of something being in multiple states at once 
            until it's observed.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            That fit surprisingly well with our original idea. Instead of people simply disappearing, 
            we turned it into something more ambiguous — are they gone, or just… not observed anymore?
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Final idea -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="500">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">What It Became</h2>
          <p>
            The final film became a mix of mystery and sci-fi — four students trapped in a classroom 
            where reality doesn't behave the way it should.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Things don't just “happen” — they depend on perception, observation, and timing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Making It (UPDATED) -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="600">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Making It</h2>
          <p>
            This part was way more chaotic than expected.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-2">
            The biggest issue? We didn't have a place to shoot. The college wasn't allowing us to use classrooms after hours, 
            and during the day it was almost impossible because of regular classes.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-2">
            We literally went around the entire campus — multiple times — asking different teachers for permission. 
            This went on for almost a month… and still nothing.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-2">
            At one point we actually thought we wouldn't be able to shoot the film at all. 
            People were starting to drop out, and everything felt stuck.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-2">
            Finally, our subject teacher stepped in and helped us get permission through someone, and that basically saved the whole project.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-2">
            After that, things still weren't perfect, but at least we could actually start shooting. 
            A lot of scenes were adjusted on the spot just to make them work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Reality -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="700">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Reality</h2>
          <p>
            Not everything went perfectly. Managing shots, keeping continuity, and timing scenes 
            properly was harder than expected.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            But that was kind of the best part — just figuring things out as we went.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Video -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="800">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Watch the Film (Use earbuds for better quality)</h2>

          <div class="mt-4 aspect-video">
            <iframe 
              class="w-full h-full rounded-xl border border-white/10"
              src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dh3Q_wGMC84"
              title="Collapse Short Film"
              allowfullscreen
            ></iframe>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Screenplay -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="900">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Screenplay</h2>
          <p>
            If you're interested in how the story was structured, here's the full screenplay.
          </p>

          <a 
            href="/Personal-Website/files/collapse_screenplay.pdf" 
            target="_blank"
            class="inline-block mt-4 px-6 py-3 bg-primary text-white rounded-xl hover:opacity-80 transition"
          >
            View Screenplay →
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Dialogues -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="1000">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Dialogues</h2>
          <p>
            We also worked with a separate dialogue draft while building the scenes.
          </p>

          <a 
            href="/Personal-Website/files/collapse_dialogues.pdf" 
            target="_blank"
            class="inline-block mt-4 px-6 py-3 bg-primary text-white rounded-xl hover:opacity-80 transition"
          >
            View Dialogues →
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Ending -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="1100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Finally</h2>
          <p>
            We were the first to finish our film even though we started last. 
            It turned out great and was deeply enjoyed by everyone.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The Best part? Our teacher loved it and praised my acting skills in front of everyone😎😎
          </p>
          <p>
            The Worst part? I wasn't present that day....😭😭
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            This started as a simple idea about people disappearing, but ended up becoming something 
            a lot more interesting. Not perfect, but definitely something I enjoyed building.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>